<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-5111] Premature EOF in RandomAccessReadBuffer using an InputStream</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5111</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are some strange differences in the test results without changing any code, e.g. org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDFontTest.testPDFox5048()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like we can&apos;t rely on InputStream.available when reading a pdf from a stream (based on an URL) using RandomAccessReadBuffer. According to the javadoc ofInputStream.available the behaviour can be different for different implementations. In our case it returns 0 and PDFBox doesn&apos;t read any more data which leads to an incomplete file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
